1770   /// Fuse two guarded fusion candidates, creating a new fused loop.
1771   ///
1772   /// Fusing guarded loops is handled much the same way as fusing non-guarded
1773   /// loops. The rewiring of the CFG is slightly different though, because of
1774   /// the presence of the guards around the loops and the exit blocks after the
1775   /// loop body. As such, the new loop is rewired as follows:
1776   ///    1. Keep the guard branch from FC0 and use the non-loop block target
1777   /// from the FC1 guard branch.
1778   ///    2. Remove the exit block from FC0 (this exit block should be empty
1779   /// right now).
1780   ///    3. Remove the guard branch for FC1
